      "content": "i get that, but i'm looking for more of an industry reality check here. if we're trying to make this show feel \"authentic\" to the audience, wouldn't the audience expect a certain look for these archetypes? \n\nlike, if you're writing a script where the character is a high-level tech CEO who's also a bit of a recluse or a genius, wouldn't it feel more \"natural\" to a viewer if they were of a certain race? or if we're talking about a character who is a \"troubled youth\" from a rough neighborhood, isn't there a specific demographic that just visually communicates that instantly without needing a lot of dialogue? i'm just trying to see if there's a way to use race to shorthand these traits for the audience.",
